This page tries to summarize the algorithm used for realistic train acceleration.

== Units used ==

''[v]'' = mph

''[P]'' = W

''[m]'' = t

== Formulas ==

''F'' = 22''P'' / 10''v'' [N]

''n'' &mdash; number of cars

''&mu;'' = 35 (eq. 1e-3 ?) &mdash; coefficient of friction

''A'' = 120 &mdash; area (units?)

''d'' = 20+3''n'' &mdash; drag coefficient

''i'' = &Sigma; 60''s<sub>i</sub>m<sub>i</sub>'' &mdash; incline term, summed over cars

''s<sub>i</sub>'' &mdash; slope, -1 (going down), 0, or 1

''m<sub>i</sub>'' &mdash; mass of the car

''Fr'' = 4(13''m'' / 10 + 60''n'' + ''&mu;mv'' / 1000 + ''Adv''<sup>2</sup>/10000 + i) [N]

''a'' = (''F'' - ''Fr'') / (''m'' * 4) [m s<sup>-2</sup>]

